AC     .US/F  : Sonic Transit Time (alias)
PHI_E  .V/V   : Effective Porosity (DN average)
VSHALE .V/V   : Shale Volume (GR linear)
SW     .V/V   : Water Saturation (Archie, Rw=0.025)
VHC    .V/V   : Hydrocarbon Volume (PhiE x (1-SW))
NET    .BIN   : Net Reservoir Flag (VSHALE<0.40)
PAY    .BIN   : Pay Flag (NET=1 AND SW<0.60)
CROSS  .V/V   : Neutron-Density Crossover (RHOB-NPHI)
~Params ----------------------------------------------------
FORM .  BOKOR-2                        : Formation / Well ID
RFT  .  1380.0  1420.0  1600.0  1720.0 : RFT sample depths (mMD)
MD_D .  1250.0                         : Measured depth datum (mMD)
TVDSS.  46.20                          : TVD at datum (mTVDSS)
DATUM.  MSL  Mean Sea Level             : Depth datum reference
# Formation Tops (EXPLORATORY_VISUALIZATION — not RFT-confirmed)
# BOKOR-2 is 1.2km NE of BOKOR-1 — slight structural updip
FM_TOP .  1360.0  : Top FMM Formation (Shale) — 45m deeper than BOKOR-1
SS1_TOP.  1520.0  : Top Shallow Sand 1 — downdip vs BOKOR-1
SS1_BOT.  1600.0  : Bottom Shallow Sand 1
SS2_TOP.  1650.0  : Top Deep Sand 2  <-- main gas reservoir (30m deeper than BOKOR-1)
SS2_BOT.  1810.0  : Bottom Deep Sand 2
SS3_TOP.  1920.0  : Top Deep Sand 3
SS3_BOT.  2080.0  : Bottom Deep Sand 3
BASE  .  2130.0  : Base of reservoir section
# Petrophysics cutoffs
RW     .  0.025  : Formation water resistivity (ohm.m)
PHIT  .  0.30   : Total porosity cutoff
VSH_cut .  0.40 : Shale volume cutoff for net pay
SW_cut  .  0.60 : Sw cutoff for pay
CLAIM  .  EXPLORATORY_VISUALIZATION    : Default claim state
~Other -----------------------------------------------------
BOKOR-2 is the second well in the BOKOR field appraisal program.
Drilled April 2024 by PAPC, 1.2km NE of BOKOR-1 on the same structural
closure. Objectives: (1) confirm lateral continuity of SS2 and SS3 fans,
(2) RFT sampling in SS2 gas column. Result: Gas confirmed in SS2 and SS3.
Shows higher porosity in SS2 vs BOKOR-1 due to cleaner sand facies.
Depths are measured from GL (46.2m above MSL). All in mMD.
